  "prompt": "How do I get bank account details from account number in SBI?",
  "response": "Accessing detailed bank account information using just an account number is restricted to protect individuals' privacy and security. If you need information related to a specific SBI (State Bank of India) account, here are the appropriate steps you can take:\n\n1. **Visit a Local Branch:**\n   - Go to the nearest SBI branch with the necessary identification documents.\n   - Speak with a bank representative who can assist you based on your authorized status and the purpose of your request.\n\n2. **Contact SBI Customer Service:**\n   - Reach out to SBI's official customer service through their verified phone numbers or email addresses available on the [official SBI website](https://www.onlinesbi.com/).\n   - Explain your situation and provide any required information to verify your identity and authorization.\n\n3. **Use Online Banking Services:**\n   - If you have access to SBI's online banking platform, you might find certain account details there.\n   - Ensure you have the necessary login credentials and permissions to view the information.\n\n4. **Provide Proper Authorization:**\n   - If you are authorized to access someone else's account information (e.g., power of attorney, legal authority), ensure you have the relevant documents ready.\n   - The bank may require these documents before providing any information.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Privacy and Security:** Banks are legally obligated to protect their customers' financial information. Unauthorized access or attempts to obtain someone else's account details can lead to legal consequences.\n  \n- **Authorized Access Only:** Ensure that you have the proper authorization to request or access the account details. Typically, only the account holder or authorized individuals (with proper documentation) can access this information.\n\n- **Avoid Sharing Sensitive Information:** Never share your own or others' bank account details, passwords, or PINs with unverified sources or through insecure channels.\n\nIf you believe there has been unauthorized access to your account or you need assistance with account-related issues, contacting SBI directly through their official channels is the safest and most effective approach.",
